among the complications are lack of historical data  long reporting delays  uncertainty as to the number and identity of insureds with potential exposure and unresolved legal issues regarding policy coverage  unresolved legal issues regarding the determination  availability and timing of exhaustion of policy limits  plaintiffs evolving and expanding theories of liability  availability and collectibility of recoveries from reinsurance  retrospectively determined premiums and other contractual agreements  and estimating the extent and timing of any contractual liability  and other uncertainties 
